The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Morientes sorry for abusing coach 
Madrid: Real Madrid coach Vicente del Bosque confirmed Friday that striker Fernando Morientes had insulted him and refused to go on as substitute towards the end of the Champions League match with Borussia Dortmund. Morientes, who had spent the final 20 minutes of Wednesdays match warming up, called his coach a son of a bitch after being told to go on in the final minute of injury-time. Del Bosque confirmed the story but said the matter had been forgotten after an apology from the player. Its true that the incident occurred. The following morning the player apologised promptly and courteously and thats that. Peace reigns. Morientes was Real Madrids top-scorer last season but he was put up for sale by the club and has featured rarely this term following the arrival of Ronaldo.  (REUTERS)  Copyright 
